#: a75d5be3ca794e87ad7dc63061926913 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:1
msgid "Solve the sparse linear system ``A x = b`` (legacy entry point)."
msgstr ""

#: 660e2df72bdb49c0b75eff8a30624446 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:5
msgid ""
"This free function pre-dates the ``torch-sla`` integration and is "
"**scheduled for removal**. The canonical path is to wrap the data in a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` and call its ``solve`` method "
"(inherited from ``torch_sla.SparseTensor``), which auto-detects symmetry "
"/ positive-definiteness and routes to ``torch_sla.spsolve`` directly. See"
" :doc:`/user_guide/linear_solvers`."
msgstr ""

#: 99ad2120b8444101a5da93fb9119ca44 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:13
msgid ""
"Low-level entry point: takes raw COO arrays instead of a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` object. With ``torch-sla`` "
"installed, dispatches to a differentiable sparse-linear-algebra backend; "
"without it, falls back to a curated mini-stack of SciPy / SuperLU / CuPy "
"/ PETSc wrappers."
msgstr ""

#: 9e22513358d347df871bd063ba1ca7d7 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:25
msgid "Dense shape ``(m, n)`` of ``A``."
msgstr ""

#: c9dfa8dc7d684bbbb7cd84c99290bff3 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:27
msgid ""
"Right-hand side. Shape ``[n]`` for a single RHS, or ``[n, n_batch]`` for "
"batched RHS (auto-routed through SuperLU)."
msgstr ""

#: 03da6aadd33344a983b326beb1a8e441 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:30
msgid ""
"Torch-sla path: ``\"auto\"`` (CPU → ``\"scipy\"``, CUDA → "
"``\"pytorch\"``), ``\"scipy\"``, ``\"pytorch\"``, ``\"eigen\"``, "
"``\"cudss\"``, ``\"cupy\"``. Fallback path (no torch-sla): ``\"auto\"``, "
"``\"petsc\"``, ``\"cupy\"`` — others are accepted but the "
"method/preconditioner hints below are ignored."
msgstr ""

#: 192ae5c4aaec45d1809a32583337761b of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:37
msgid ""
"Iterative algorithm — ``\"cg\"``, ``\"bicgstab\"``, ``\"minres\"``, "
"``\"gmres\"``, ``\"lgmres\"`` — or one of the direct factorizations "
"``\"lu\"``, ``\"umfpack\"``, ``\"cholesky\"``, ``\"ldlt\"``. See the "
"installed ``torch_sla.spsolve`` signature for the canonical list. "
"**Honoured only on the torch-sla path.** On the fallback path, each "
"wrapper uses a fixed algorithm."
msgstr ""

#: 24f7b258f6bf419c8ec599a94df29540 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:44
msgid ""
"``\"jacobi\"``, ``\"ilu\"``, or ``\"none\"``. Same caveat as ``method`` —"
" torch-sla path only."
msgstr ""

#: 600d18041f48452084d9dfde359d45e8 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:47
msgid "Convergence tolerance (iterative methods)."
msgstr ""

#: 0e92e265034c4a3f90e251049dd13202 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:49
msgid "Iteration budget (iterative methods)."
msgstr ""

#: 7637d666082448eeaab123c1c3ea355d of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:51
msgid ""
"Initial guess. Currently consumed only by some fallback wrappers and "
"ignored by torch-sla."
msgstr ""

#: ad1dd07ebd03496089bcc0fe4d5aa5a5 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:54
msgid ""
"Hint to the torch-sla path that ``A`` is symmetric positive definite. "
"Picks CG as the default ``method``; set ``False`` for indefinite / non-"
"symmetric ``A`` and combine with ``method=\"bicgstab\"`` or "
"``\"gmres\"``."
msgstr ""

#: 4dc8a7cbe6a34976afbd04154daaa855 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:59
msgid "Print which backend/method was picked."
msgstr ""

#: dc3b9f8902474e84b43063a7d1382088 of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:62
msgid "Solution ``x``, same shape and dtype as ``b``."
msgstr ""

#: bc26dd2d0c6440669cb9afb01f2ba4da of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:66
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: 76e6d6896078499286234cd5205068be of tensormesh.sparse.solve.spsolve:67
msgid ""
"Both paths are autograd-aware: gradients of ``x`` flow back into "
"``edata`` and ``b`` via an adjoint sparse solve. On the torch-sla path "
"this is built in to the library; on the fallback path each wrapper "
"supplies its own :class:`torch.autograd.Function` backward."
msgstr ""

#: cc6adf1572f64afeab7b7b283dcfd1af of
#: tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve.nonlinear_solve:1
